<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="1208" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1208">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">702.4193/9–1249: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-12T18:00:00-04:00">September
                                    12, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>625. British have agreed accept custody US property Mukden (Deptel
                                601<note n="87" xml:id="d1208fn87">Dated September 2, 3 p. m.; it
                                reported that the British had been requested to accept custody of
                                U.S. property in Mukden but had not replied
                            (702.4193/9–249).</note>). If possible Ward should obtain receipts from
                            British Consul.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>